     <section name="Description">

  <p>The jbundle <strong>OSGi to JNLP Web Start Servlet</strong> makes automatically allows your OSGi
  applications to run as Web Start applets or applications.</p>

<p>
It's a pain to set up Web Start to run java applets in a web browser. We have to specify the
package to module mappings in a JNLP file to make everything work.
</p>
<p>
Wouldn't it be nice if Web Start were as easy to set up as OSGi. Well now it is. The OSGi to JNLP
converter will automatically create JNLP and jar files from OSGi dependencies.
</p>
<p>
All you have to do is specify java the main class. For example:<br/>
<code>
http://www.jbundle.org/jnlp/biorhythm?mainClass=org.jbundle.util.biorhythm.Biorhythm<br/>
</code>
is all you would need to type to launch the OSGi Biorhythm program from a web browser.
This servlet takes care of all the Web Start configuration automatically. It even automatically
updates the cached jnlp and java jar files when the OSGi bundles are updated.
</p>

    </section>
